    text: "The Dar Es Salaam Bank heist happened in Baghdad, Iraq, in 2007. The bank employees came to work in the morning and found the front door was unlocked. When they went inside, they saw that the vault was open and empty. Three guards who worked at the bank were missing. They had stolen about 282 million dollars in cash. This was a huge amount of money. The guards waited until everyone left the bank the night before. Then, they loaded the money into cars and drove away. Because the country was in a war, there were many checkpoints on the roads. Some people think the guards must have had help from the police or soldiers to move so much money with no interruptions. The money and the guards were never found. It is one of the biggest unsolved mysteries in Iraq.",
