    text: "The Great Brink's Robbery happened in Boston in 1950. At that time, it was the biggest robbery in America. A gang of 11 men planned the crime. They watched the Brink's building for 18 months. They learned when the money trucks arrived. They even stole the keys to make copies. On the night of the robbery, they wore masks and uniforms that looked like Brink's employees. They wore special rubber shoes so they made no noise. They surprised the guards and tied them up. They stole more than 2 million dollars. They disappeared into the night. The police looked for them for a long time but found nothing. The robbers almost succeeded. But years later, one of the members got angry with the others. He told the police everything. The police arrested the gang just a few days before the time limit for the crime ran out.",
