    text: "The Lufthansa Heist happened in New York in 1978. It took place at the airport. A worker at the airport owed money to the mob, so he told them about money flying in from Germany. The heist was planned by Jimmy Burke, a powerful criminal. A group of masked men arrived in a van late at night. They captured the employees and forced the manager to open the vault. They stole about 5 million dollars in cash and jewelry. It was the largest cash robbery in America at that time. This story is famous because of the movie 'Goodfellas.' After the robbery, Jimmy Burke was afraid the others would talk to the police. He ordered the murder of almost everyone involved in the crime. Because of this, very little of the money was ever recovered.",
