    text: "The Northern Bank robbery happened in Belfast, Northern Ireland, in 2004. It was a very well-planned crime. A group of men went to the homes of two bank managers. They took the managers' families as hostages. They told the managers to go to work the next day and act normal. If they provided no help, their families would be killed. The managers went to the bank and let the robbers in after it closed. The robbers loaded 26.5 million pounds into a van. They drove away and released the families unharmed. The police believe the robbery was done by the IRA, a paramilitary group. The robbery caused a big problem because the bank had to change all its paper money to stop the robbers from spending the stolen cash.",
